						<summary>

						<p>On the fourth pillar of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1450, Sarvadhāri, Kārttika ba. 30, Thursday = 1528 A.D., November 12. Solar eclipse.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers the grant of land called <hi rend="italic">dari-maḍi</hi> by Kākila Palrāju on the occasion of <hi rend="italic">Sūrya-grahaṇa</hi> (Solar eclipse) for the merit of his father Padmarāju and mother Tirumaladēvī. </p>						

